# Front-end
Using React.js 
In the project directory MY-APP, you can run
### `npm start`
Runs the app in the development mode
Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000) to view it in your browser.

# Back-end
Using Node.js and Express web framework to establish a server
In the backend directory MY-APP/backend, you can run
### `node server.js`
Start the server and connect to MongoDB 

# MongoDB
Install and start MongoDB on local machine
After starting MongoDB, run queries via:
1. Mongo Shell: `mongosh`
2. MongoDB Compass - GUI (optional)

# Test the Application
1. Start/Stop MongoDB
`brew services start mongodb-community@8.0`
`brew services stop mongodb-community@8.0`
2. Start backend server port 4000
`node server.js`
3. Start React development server port 3000
`npm start`


